cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.SE

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the complexity of module checking against temporal logics, which is a topic closely related to logic in computer science.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper discusses the verification of open systems, which is a common problem in AI.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper provides asymptotically optimal bounds on the computational cost of module checking, which involves algorithmic analysis.
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses automata-theoretic approaches, which are commonly used in programming language theory.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is relevant as the paper deals with the verification of software systems, which is a key topic in software engineering.
